Pentecostals. Also included are comparisons between Canadian and American, British, and Australian evangelicalism and essays on evangelical networks, leaders and revivals, women, and evangelicalism in the 1990s. Growing out of a conference sponsored by the Pew Charitable Trusts in 1995 at Queen's University, the essays elaborate a variety of important themes in the study of historical and contemporary evangelicalism and weave them together to provide an informative and challenging exploration of aspects of the evangelical experience in Canada. Contributors include Phyllis D. Airhart, Alvyn J. Austin, David W. Bebbington, Edith L. Blumhofer, Robert K. Burkinshaw, Sharon Anne Cook, Nancy Christie, P. Lorraine Coops, Duff Crerar, Michael Gauvreau, Daniel C. Goodwin, Andrew S. Grenville, Bruce L. Guenther, Bryan V. Hillis, D. Bruce Hindmarsh, Mark Hutchinson, William H. Katerberg, Kevin Kee, Ronald A.N. Kydd, Barry Mack, Mark A. Noll, David Plaxton, Darrel R. Reid, John G. Stackhouse, Jr, Marguerite Van Die, Richard W. Vaudry, and Marilyn Färdig Whiteley.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Protestant.2bisacsh1 aAirhart, Phyllis D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAustin, Alvyn J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBebbington, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumhofer, Edith L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkinshaw, Robert K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristie, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Sharon Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoops, P. Lorraine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 